Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @carrot{1}. Using #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating, until you get to the core; discard core. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (quarter both limes for 4 servings). Peel and grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Grate @garlic{1%clove}.

> Use 2 cloves garlic for 4 servings.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain well.

> Shake strainer to remove excess water.

Meanwhile, add @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} to a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Toast, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add carrot ribbons and scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, massage @peanut butter{2.3%ounce} in packet to loosen.

> If peanut butter is very cold, squeeze into a small, microwave-safe bowl. Microwave until softened, about 20 seconds.

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together peanut butter, @sesame oil{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, ginger, garlic, half the @white wine vinegar{2.5%teaspoon} (use all for 4 servings), juice from 2 lime wedges, and @sugar{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until smooth.

Roughly chop @peanuts{1%ounce}. Add noodles, veggies, half the sesame seeds, and half the peanuts to bowl with sauce; toss with #tongs{} to combine.

> If noodles are not fully coated in sauce, add water a splash at a time to bowl and continue tossing.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}, removing seeds for less heat. Divide noodles between shallow #bowls{}. Top with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds and peanuts. Sprinkle with a pinch of chili if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.